    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1423594307" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1423594307" />
    <a title="Dan Schwent" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/870755-dan-schwent"><img alt="Dan Schwent" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624242909p2/870755.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1423594307?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dan Schwent" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dan Schwent" href="/user/show/870755-dan-schwent">Dan Schwent</a>
      </span>

          marked it as to-read




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1423594307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10097869072601002591">This one is going back on the pile. I made it over 100 pages this time. That&apos;s something, right?<br/><br/>My problems with this book are the glacial pace and overwritten sentences. It&apos;s like an even more wordy Donna Tartt book. I don&apos;t need literary references cited in every paragraph and overblown dialogue and flowery language for the sake of flowery language don&apos;t impress me at this stage in the game. The pretentious, pompous tone of the book is also a turn-off. Picking up the book to read it began feel</span>
  <span id="freeText10097869072601002591" style="display:none">This one is going back on the pile. I made it over 100 pages this time. That's something, right?<br /><br />My problems with this book are the glacial pace and overwritten sentences. It's like an even more wordy Donna Tartt book. I don't need literary references cited in every paragraph and overblown dialogue and flowery language for the sake of flowery language don't impress me at this stage in the game. The pretentious, pompous tone of the book is also a turn-off. Picking up the book to read it began feeling like a chore before I finally threw in the towel.<br /><br />I'm a man with a finite lifespan and thus a finite amount of books I'll be able to read before I reach the clearing at the end of the path. I think I'll go read something more engaging.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10097869072601002591" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

